tmp-glibc/deploy/images/qemux86-64/

# Your actual image
mydistro-image-qemux86-64.ext4          ← your root filesystem image

# The kernel
bzImage                                  ← compressed kernel binary
bzImage-7.0.3-qemux86-64.bin            ← same with version stamp

# Bootloader / firmware
ovmf.qemuboot.conf                       ← QEMU boot config (x86)

# Manifest — list of every package in the image
mydistro-image-qemux86-64.manifest      ← useful for auditing

# Symlinks pointing to the latest build
mydistro-image-qemux86-64.ext4          → real file with timestamp
bzImage                                  → real file with timestamp

Detail:
.ext4 Your entire root filesystem as a disk imageFlash to device or run in QEMU
bzImage The compiled Linux kernel 7 binary Goes on the boot partition
.manifest Text list of every package + versionAuditing, CVE tracking
.qemuboot.conf QEMU launch parametersAuto-used by runqemu


